text: Gladys Luscombe (13 November 1908 - 6 June 1946) was a British diver. She competed in the women's 3 metre springboard event at the 1924 Summer Olympics. ==References== Category:1908 births Category:1946 deaths Category:British female divers Category:Olympic divers of Great Britain Category:Divers at the 1924 Summer Olympics Category:People from Newton Abbot
